casebody.data:
Cleveland Bar Association v. Trombetta.

[Cite as Cleveland Bar Assn. v. Trombetta (1994), 71 Ohio St.3d 386.]

(No. 94-2256 Submitted December 7, 1994 Decided December 30, 1994.) *388Marvin L. Karp and William Fulton, for relator. Ignatius B. Trombetta, pro se. Per Curiam.

Having thoroughly reviewed the record, we agree with the board’s finding of misconduct and its recommendation. Accordingly, respondent is hereby publicly reprimanded. Costs taxed to respondent.

Judgment accordingly.

Moyer, C.J., A.W. Sweeney, Douglas, Wright, Resnick and F.E. Sweeney, JJ., concur. Pfeifer, J., dissents. Pfeifer, J., dissenting. I would dismiss the case.
